/** \mainpage BlueWiz2.1 + EDR Firmware Implementation Document
<h2> Introduction </h2>
<p>Bluetooth is a short-range radio link intended to replace the cable-connected
portable and/or fixed electronic devices. The Bluetooth architecture, as
standardized by the Bluetooth SIG defines HCI-LMP and Link Control firmware
on top of the baseband link control hardware.</p>

<p>This document is intended as a API reference for BlueWiz Firmware
implementation. The firmware is divided into the following modules:</p>

<ul>
<li> \ref hci - HCI reference
<li> \ref lmp - LMP reference
<li> \ref lc - LC reference
<li> \ref bb_driver - BB Driver reference
<li> \ref hci_td - HCI TD reference
<li> \ref bz_ref_platform - Platform Abstraction reference
<li> \ref bz_utils - Utilities reference
<li> \ref mint_os - MINT OS reference
</ul>


